<br>
SDSS J082053.53+000843.4 belongs to the HW Vir family of short period binary<br>
systems and was first identified by Geier in 2011. Whilst three subsequent<br>
papers have focused on the morphology of this system, little has been published<br>
on the system period and its constancy. Here we provide the first published<br>
times of minima together with a revised ephemeris and a binary period,<br>
0.0962404(1)d, that is four orders of magnitude more precise than previous<br>
declared values.<br>
