<br>
We apply our recently suggested statistical approach to thermal evolution of<br>
isolated neutron stars and accreting quasistationary neutron stars in X-ray<br>
transients for constraining the position and relative broadening alpha of the<br>
direct Urca threshold of powerful neutrino emission in neutron star cores. We<br>
show that most likely explanation of observations corresponds to alpha = 0.08 -<br>
0.10 and to the neutron star mass, at which the direct Urca process is open,<br>
M_D = (1.6 - 1.8) M_sun.<br>
